<title>USA: Motorola unit to add 300 jobs at U.K. plant.</title>
<headline>Motorola unit to add 300 jobs at U.K. plant.</headline>
<dateline>SCHAUMBURG, Ill. 1997-02-05</dateline>
<text>
<p>Motorola Inc said Wednesday its Cellular Infrastructure Group (CIG) will create 300 jobs at its Swindon, England, mobile communications plant.</p>
<p>Motorola CIG said its GSM Products Division will expand the workforce at the facility to 1,700 and lease an additional 33,000 square feet of space.</p>
<p>The moves are a response to an increase in sales orders for the company's digital Global System for Mobile (GSM) communications infrastructure equipment, Motorola said.</p>
<p>Motorola makes communications products, semiconductors and electronic systems and components.</p>
<p>Its shares were trading down 2-3/8 to 65-1/4.</p>
<p>((Chicago newsdesk (312) 408-8787))</p>
